SHUTDOWN(1)                      User Commands                      SHUTDOWN(1)

NAME
       shutdown - halt, power-off or reboot the machine

SYNOPSIS
       shutdown [OPTION]... [TIME] [WALL]...

DESCRIPTION
       shutdown  may  be  used  to  halt, power-off or reboot the machine.
       The first argument may be a TIME string.  The optional WALL
       argument is a wall message to send to all users.

   TIME
       The time at which to shut down may be specified as:

       now    shut down immediately

       +m     shut down in m minutes from now

       hh:mm  shut down at the specified time (24-hour clock)

       If TIME is not specified, "+1" (one minute delay) is implied.

OPTIONS
       -H, --halt
              halt the machine

       -P, --poweroff
              power-off the machine (default)

       -r, --reboot
              reboot the machine

       -h     equivalent to --poweroff, overridden by --halt

       -k     don't halt, power-off, reboot; just write the wall message

       -c     cancel a pending shutdown

       --show show pending shutdown

       --no-wall
              don't send wall message

       --help display this help and exit

NOTES
       If a shutdown is scheduled, a file /run/nologin is created to
       prevent new user logins.  The file is removed when the shutdown
       is cancelled.

EXIT STATUS
       0      if OK

       1      if errors occurred

AUTHORS
       LikeOS-64 project.

SEE ALSO
       halt(1), poweroff(1), reboot(1)

